This article is a fact sheet released by the White House Office of the Press Secretary in 2015, discussing the impact and benefits of the Affordable Care Act (ACA), also known as Obamacare. It highlights how the ACA has improved the American healthcare system and provides examples of the positive changes it has brought about. These include guaranteed access to preventive care, a decline in the uninsured rate, safer hospital stays, savings for seniors on prescription medication, numerous affordable coverage options, increased Medicaid coverage, savings for hospitals, and the transformative implications of President Obama's health care policies on the U.S. economy. The fact sheet also emphasizes the ongoing efforts to improve health care and promote preventive care, secure coverage for all Americans, drive down the cost of care, and encourage the remaining states to expand Medicaid eligibility.